# 3) use the concatenate function c() to create a vector called weight containing the weight (in lb) of 10 children: , 120, 117, 139, 129, 94, 86, 106, 107, 126.  Do the same for height in inches;, 47, 40, 41, 35, 60, 42, 50, 49, 38, 42.  Then calculate the bmi (weight/ the square of the height) of the kids.

height <- c(47, 40, 41, 35, 60, 42, 50, 49, 38, 42)
bmi <- (weight/(height^2))
